"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0806-1463742-olympics-podcast-glory-glory-kellie-harrington\", \"text\": \"  Kellie Harrington is a back-to-back Olympic champion after a dominant victory over Wenlu Yang of China - Raf Diallo was in Roland Garros to witness a night of history for irish boxing and Irish sport.  He finds a quiet spot as the home of French tennis is taken over by Irish fans to fill Mikey Stafford in on the night that ireland moved up to 12th on the medal table.  Mikey also chats to David Gillick about a couple of difficult days for Irish athletics, as he also looks ahead to Rhasidat Adeleke's 400m semi-final.  Listen to the RT\\u00c9 Olympics Podcast on theRT\\u00c9 Radio Player,Apple Podcasts,Spotify, orwherever you get your podcasts  We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity. Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"